3
00:00:07,060 --> 00:00:11,260
In the most horrifying way you can imagine

4
00:00:16,420 --> 00:00:17,160
This is China Uncensored.

5
00:00:17,170 --> 00:00:18,369
I’m Chris Chappell.

6
00:00:18,369 --> 00:00:19,630
You know, say what you will

7
00:00:19,630 --> 00:00:21,540
about the Chinese Communist Party,

8
00:00:21,540 --> 00:00:25,070
you have to admire their relentless optimism.

9
00:00:25,070 --> 00:00:27,720
Take the coronavirus outbreak for instance.

10
00:00:27,720 --> 00:00:30,460
Now *you* might be completely overwhelmed

11
00:00:30,460 --> 00:00:32,320
by this immense human tragedy.

12
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:35,600
But the Communist Party can see the silver
lining.

13
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:38,690
For example, greenhouse gas emissions are
down!

14
00:00:38,690 --> 00:00:40,899
How’s that for some good news?

15
00:00:40,899 --> 00:00:42,010
Or how about this,

16
00:00:42,010 --> 00:00:43,850
China spares no effort to improve

17
00:00:43,850 --> 00:00:46,090
governance capability amid epidemic.

18
00:00:46,090 --> 00:00:48,570
That sounds impressive right?

19
00:00:48,570 --> 00:00:50,989
Until you realize that “governance capability”

20
00:00:50,989 --> 00:00:54,410
is a nice way of saying Mao-style social control.

21
00:00:54,410 --> 00:00:56,180
Now to be fair to the Communist Party,

22
00:00:56,180 --> 00:01:00,239
it’s not clear if it is using the coronavirus
as an *excuse*

23
00:01:00,239 --> 00:01:02,649
to ratchet up the authoritarianism.

24
00:01:02,649 --> 00:01:04,970
Or if ratcheting up the authoritarianism

25
00:01:04,970 --> 00:01:07,659
is the only way they know how to deal with
the coronavirus.

26
00:01:07,659 --> 00:01:09,350
It’s a “which came first,

27
00:01:09,350 --> 00:01:11,880
the chicken or the egg” situation.

28
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:14,000
Either way, I think we can all agree that

29
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,130
the people in China had too much freedom.

30
00:01:17,130 --> 00:01:20,530
Which is why, as authorities “crack down”
on the coronavirus,

31
00:01:20,530 --> 00:01:25,210
they’re abducting and beating up citizens
across the country.

32
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:27,420
And holding them to the ground and...

33
00:01:27,420 --> 00:01:29,150
spraying them with disinfectant?

34
00:01:29,150 --> 00:01:33,649
I don’t think that’s how this works.

35
00:01:33,649 --> 00:01:35,899
Or simply welded into their homes,

36
00:01:35,899 --> 00:01:38,950
where I really hope they have enough food.

37
00:01:38,950 --> 00:01:40,420
These people were playing Mahjong,

38
00:01:40,420 --> 00:01:42,210
when authorities busted in

39
00:01:42,210 --> 00:01:45,550
and really showed that table who’s boss.

40
00:01:45,550 --> 00:01:48,580
That’s because mahjong and card games have
been banned.

41
00:01:48,580 --> 00:01:51,649
There’s a reason why an epidemic disease

42
00:01:51,649 --> 00:01:53,540
is being treated the same way the Party

43
00:01:53,540 --> 00:01:55,990
treats political dissidents.

44
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:57,610
Chinese leader Xi Jinping has fired

45
00:01:57,610 --> 00:01:59,829
both the party secretary of Hubei province

46
00:01:59,829 --> 00:02:02,320
and the party secretary of the city of Wuhan,

47
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:04,409
where the coronavirus outbreak began.

48
00:02:04,409 --> 00:02:06,049
In case you don’t know,

49
00:02:06,049 --> 00:02:07,610
the Party secretary outranks

50
00:02:07,610 --> 00:02:10,230
the governor or mayor of the same region.

51
00:02:10,230 --> 00:02:11,730
In Communist China,

52
00:02:11,730 --> 00:02:14,830
it’s the Party members who are really in
charge.

53
00:02:14,830 --> 00:02:16,290
So who did Xi Jinping replace

54
00:02:16,290 --> 00:02:18,800
the Party secretary of Hubei province with?

55
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:21,850
Why, Xi Jinping’s close ally Ying Yong.

56
00:02:21,850 --> 00:02:24,020
He’s a good friend of Xi Jinping’s.

57
00:02:24,020 --> 00:02:25,020
He,

58
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:27,530
“rose through the political ranks in Zhejiang
Province,

59
00:02:27,530 --> 00:02:30,790
where Mr. Xi himself began his climb to power.”

60
00:02:30,790 --> 00:02:34,190
And Ying Yong got loads of experience dealing
with sick people

61
00:02:34,190 --> 00:02:36,970
when he worked in the “Public Security Bureau,

62
00:02:36,970 --> 00:02:42,110
